    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5f5d054b_986557a8",
        "filename": "resultdb/cli/cmd_stream.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 74,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-19T01:52:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "IMO, users would be more interested in whether their test commands support SinkAPIs integrated, because this flag is a command-line flag, and users will use this stream as a command-line tool.\n\nHow about this?\n\n```\nRun a given test command and update the results to ResultDB. Either use the current invocation from LUCI_CONTEXT or create/finalize a new one. Example:\n  rdb stream ./out/chrome/test/browser_tests\n\nTest binaries are required to integrate Sink APIs into themselves, or no test results will be uploaded. For a list of test frameworks with Sink APIs support,  visit https://foo/bar/sink-supported-test-frameworks.md.\n```\n\nThe MD file can include a list of known test frameworks, such as gtest, etc, and a link to a codelab for how to integrate SinkAPIs into test binaries/frameworks, which could also include a link to the protocol description.\n\nWDYT?",
      "parentUuid": "18f144c9_e1e3a6ea",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 74,
        "startChar": 67,
        "endLine": 74,
        "endChar": 70
      },
      "revId": "0c379443d243b0a4da8cac534b58ea2f38cc7c61",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8c682937_bcf0db86",
        "filename": "resultdb/cli/cmd_stream.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 74,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-20T17:09:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think, for user who wants to integrate, this still does not explain what is \"Sink API\".\n\nI also doubt this tool will be used by chromium developers directly. This tool accepts a raw path to the binary. As a chrome developer, I\u0027d expect to only provide a ninja/GN target, and expect the binary to be compiled/linked/executed for me (like blaze test). So I think people who are interested in the list of commands supporting the protocol won\u0027t be reading this help message. Instead, I think this help messages will be read by people who try to integrate with rdb stream.\n\nin general, i think a program should explain what it does, rather than letting the user infer its behavior based on higher-level descriptions",
      "parentUuid": "5f5d054b_986557a8",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 74,
        "startChar": 67,
        "endLine": 74,
