      "writtenOn": "2020-04-18T15:20:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i don\u0027t see a guarantee in *this* code that the input was invalid. initClients might fail for other reasons, e.g. https://chromium.googlesource.com/infra/luci/luci-go/+/refs/changes/59/2155559/7/resultdb/cli/baserun.go#140\nor it might be changed in the future to fail for other reasons.\n\nalso this is inconsistent with other subcommands: others return same exit code.\nstepping back, in what scenario the caller needs to distinguish input errors and internal errors?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 110,
        "startChar": 21,
        "endLine": 110,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "0c379443d243b0a4da8cac534b58ea2f38cc7c61",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
