    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ef229023_1716eb04",
        "filename": "resultdb/cli/cmd_stream.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 110,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-19T01:52:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t have a scenario where the caller needs to distinguish input errors and internal errors. I wlll update stream to return 1001 in any case if it was not able to run the test command.\n\n\u003e\u003e also this is inconsistent with other subcommands: others return same exit code.\nDoes Swarming task need to distinguish the exit codes between test binary and stream?\ne.g., if an exit code indicates that there was an error from stream itself, mark the Swarming Task as failed.\n\nPerhaps, Swarming task only needs to know whether stream successfully executed the test command or not. Then, stream can use baserun.done() to exit 0 or 1, like other subcommands do.\n\nIt wouldn\u0027t even need to return 1001 for internal errors, either. The child exit codes will only be used to determine invocation.interrupted in the invocation finalize process.\n\nPlease correct me if I misunderstood what exit codes should be returned from Stream to Swarming task.",
      "parentUuid": "6ff40fb6_d3805fed",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 110,
        "startChar": 21,
        "endLine": 110,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "0c379443d243b0a4da8cac534b58ea2f38cc7c61",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
